NAF.raw: http : / / www . dailymail . co . uk / sport / boxing / article - 2170324 / Wladimir - Klitschko - retains - titles - stopping - Tony - Thompson - rounds . html Wladimir Klitschko retains titles stopping Thompson in six rounds PUBLISHED : 22 : 07 GMT , 7 July 2012 UPDATED : 22 : 07 GMT , 7 July 2012 Wladimir Klitschko stopped Tony Thompson in the sixth round to retain his WBA , IBF and WBO heavyweight title belts on Saturday . Klitschko put Thompson on the canvas with a big right hand near the end of the fifth round at Stade de Suisse , and the 40 - year - old American never recovered . The Ukrainian champion dropped Thompson again in the sixth , and referee Sam Williams gave the challenger a standing count before stopping the fight . Klitschko finished the fight five rounds sooner than when knocking out Thompson in the 11th of their first title fight in 2008 . The 36 - year - old champion Klitschko improved to 58 - 3 ( 51 KO ) . Thompson , who was the mandatory challenger nominated by the IBF , fell to 36 - 3 ( 24 KO ) .
